TITLE: Reading a File's Entire Contents from a Readable Stream in Node.js
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to read a file's entire contents from a Readable stream by collecting chunks across multiple 'readable' events and concatenating them when the 'end' event is emitted.
SOURCE: https://github.com/caido/doc-developer/blob/main/src/reference/modules/llrt/stream.md#2025-04-20_snippet_16

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const chunks = [];

readable.on('readable', () => {
  let chunk;
  while (null !== (chunk = readable.read())) {
    chunks.push(chunk);
  }
});

readable.on('end', () => {
  const content = chunks.join('');
});
```

