TITLE: Running 'ls -lh /usr' Command with Node.js spawn()
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to run the 'ls -lh /usr' command using child_process.spawn(). It captures stdout, stderr, and the exit code of the spawned process.
SOURCE: https://github.com/caido/doc-developer/blob/main/src/reference/modules/llrt/child_process.md#2025-04-20_snippet_45

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const { spawn } = require('child_process');
const ls = spawn('ls', ['-lh', '/usr']);

ls.stdout.on('data', (data) => {
  console.log(`stdout: ${data}`);
});

ls.stderr.on('data', (data) => {
  console.error(`stderr: ${data}`);
});

ls.on('close', (code) => {
  console.log(`child process exited with code ${code}`);
});
```

